HEADWORD: nervine
<hw>nerv"ine</hw> <pr>(n⟦etil⟧rv"⟦icr⟧n; 277)</pr> <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[L. <ets>nervinus</ets> made of sinews: cf.F. <ets>nervin</ets>.
See <er>Nerve</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>Having the quality of
acting upon or affecting the nerves; quieting nervous excitement.</def>
-- <def2><pos>n.</pos> <def>A nervine agent.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
